<title>USA: Texas Commerce reports drop in fraud losses.</title>
<headline>Texas Commerce reports drop in fraud losses.</headline>
<dateline>DALLAS 1997-06-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Texas Commerce Bank Bank, a unit of Chase Manhattan Corp, said Monday that a new system for the detection of fraudulent checks passed by tellers has lowered losses considerably in its branch system.</p>
<p>The bank said that it has experienced sharp declines in fraud attempts &quot;beyond its forecasts or expectations.&quot;</p>
<p>According to privately-held Carreker-Antinori Inc, which installed the system in January, the bank could realize potential annualized savings of $1.8 million, or $335,000 per month, at each branch.</p>
